	<Title>
		Recipe: Avocado dip
	</Title>
	<Abstract />
	<ServingInfo Label="Serves">
		6
	</ServingInfo>
	<DietitianTip Label="Dietitian&apos;s tip">
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dietitian&apos;s tip:&lt;/strong&gt; Avocado, also known as the alligator pear, is high in monounsaturated fat and a good source of lutein, an antioxidant that may protect vision. This mixture is a great dressing for mixed green salads and is a good topping for fish or chicken.&lt;/p&gt;
	</DietitianTip>
	<Directions Label="Directions">
		&lt;p&gt;In a small bowl, combine the sour cream, onion, hot sauce and avocado. Mix to blend the ingredients evenly. Serve with baked tortilla chips or sliced vegetables.&lt;/p&gt;
	</Directions>
	<Ingredients Label="Ingredients">
		&lt;p&gt;1/2 cup fat-free sour cream&lt;br /&gt;
2 teaspoons chopped onion&lt;br /&gt;
1/8 teaspoon hot sauce&lt;br /&gt;
1 ripe avocado, peeled, pitted and mashed&lt;/p&gt;
	</Ingredients>
